{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844421251,"sessionID":"ses_2876d02baffe1H9mB6WOHDddQ4","part":{"id":"prt_d7893606f0015eF2c50e1CKdBk","messageID":"msg_d78934394001dUOQN08YI79b03","sessionID":"ses_2876d02baffe1H9mB6WOHDddQ4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This document describes the HTTP service framework design for WorkloadManager.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ```\n10: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n11: │                        HTTP Server                           │\n12: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐  │\n13: │  │   Router    │──│ Middleware  │──│      Handlers       │  │\n14: │  │             │  │   Chain     │  │                     │  │\n15: │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘  │\n16: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n17:                               │\n18:                               ▼\n19:                     ┌─────────────────────┐\n20:                     │  Business Logic     │\n21:                     │  (Future AR)        │\n22:                     └─────────────────────┘\n23: ```\n24: \n25: ## Component Design\n26: \n27: ### 1. Server (`pkg/workloadmanager/server/`)\n28: \n29: Responsible for HTTP server lifecycle management.\n30: \n31: **Responsibilities:**\n32: - Server initialization with configuration\n33: - Route registration\n34: - Middleware setup\n35: - Graceful shutdown handling\n36: \n37: ### 2. Router (`pkg/workloadmanager/server/router.go`)\n38: \n39: Defines API routes and maps them to handlers.\n40: \n41: **Routes:**\n42: | Method | Path | Description |\n43: |--------|------|-------------|\n44: | GET | /health | Health check endpoint |\n45: | POST | /api/v1/workloads | Create workload |\n46: | GET | /api/v1/workloads | List workloads |\n47: | GET | /api/v1/workloads/:id | Get workload |\n48: | PUT | /api/v1/workloads/:id | Update workload |\n49: | DELETE | /api/v1/workloads/:id | Delete workload |\n50: \n51: ### 3. Middleware (`pkg/workloadmanager/middleware/`)\n52: \n53: Provides cross-cutting concerns.\n54: \n55: **Planned Middleware:**\n56: - `Logger`: Request/response logging\n57: - `Recovery`: Panic recovery\n58: - `RequestID`: Unique request ID generation\n59: - `Timeout`: Request timeout enforcement\n60: \n61: ### 4. Handlers (`pkg/workloadmanager/handlers/`)\n62: \n63: HTTP request handlers (stubs for now).\n64: \n65: ### 5. Config (`pkg/workloadmanager/config/`)\n66: \n67: Configuration management.\n68: \n69: ## Response Format\n70: \n71: ```json\n72: {\n73:   \"success\": true,\n74:   \"data\": { ... },\n75:   \"error\": null,\n76:   \"request_id\": \"uuid\"\n77: }\n78: ```\n79: \n80: ## Error Handling\n81: \n82: | Error Type | HTTP Status | Description |\n83: |------------|-------------|-------------|\n84: | ValidationError | 400 | Invalid request parameters |\n85: | NotFoundError | 404 | Resource not found |\n86: | InternalError | 500 | Server internal error |\n87: \n88: ## Decisions\n89: \n90: *To be filled during implementation*\n91: \n92: ## Open Questions\n93: \n94: 1. Which HTTP framework to use? (Gin, Chi, or std lib)\n95: 2. TLS support requirements?\n96: 3. Rate limiting strategy?\n\n(End of file - total 96 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 Design Document\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the HTTP service framework design for WorkloadManager.\n\n## Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                        HTTP Server                           │\n│  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────────────┐  │\n│  │   Router    │──│ Middleware  │──│      Handlers       │  │\n│  │             │  │   Chain     │  │                     │  │\n│  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────────────┘  │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                              │\n                              ▼\n                    ┌─────────────────────┐\n                    │  Business Logic     │","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/design.md","time":{"start":1775844421226,"end":1775844421249}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775844421254,"sessionID":"ses_2876d02baffe1H9mB6WOHDddQ4","part":{"id":"prt_d789364e8001w0cyYN0czzl25R","messageID":"msg_d78934394001dUOQN08YI79b03","sessionID":"ses_2876d02baffe1H9mB6WOHDddQ4","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-004 Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Phase 1: Project Structure Setup\n4: \n5: - [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/` directory structure\n6: - [ ] Create subpackages: `server/`, `handlers/`, `middleware/`, `config/`\n7: - [ ] Define interface contracts between layers\n8: \n9: ## Phase 2: HTTP Server Foundation\n10: \n11: - [ ] Implement base server structure with configurable options\n12: - [ ] Setup HTTP router (choose framework: Gin/Chi/std lib)\n13: - [ ] Implement server lifecycle (start, stop, graceful shutdown)\n14: - [ ] Add health check endpoint\n15: \n16: ## Phase 3: Middleware Implementation\n17: \n18: - [ ] Request logging middleware\n19: - [ ] Error recovery/panic handling middleware\n20: - [ ] Request ID generation middleware\n21: - [ ] CORS middleware (if needed)\n22: - [ ] Request timeout middleware\n23: \n24: ## Phase 4: API Endpoints & Handlers\n25: \n26: - [ ] Define RESTful routes for workload operations:\n27:   - POST /api/v1/workloads - Create workload\n28:   - GET /api/v1/workloads - List workloads\n29:   - GET /api/v1/workloads/:id - Get workload details\n30:   - PUT /api/v1/workloads/:id - Update workload\n31:   - DELETE /api/v1/workloads/:id - Delete workload\n32: - [ ] Implement handler stubs (business logic to be filled in later AR)\n33: \n34: ## Phase 5: Response & Error Handling\n35: \n36: - [ ] Define standardized JSON response structure\n37: - [ ] Implement error response formatter\n38: - [ ] Map internal errors to HTTP status codes\n39: - [ ] Add validation error handling\n40: \n41: ## Phase 6: Configuration\n42: \n43: - [ ] Define server configuration schema\n44: - [ ] Implement configuration loading from file/env\n45: - [ ] Support for port, timeout, and middleware settings\n46: \n47: ## Phase 7: Testing & Validation\n48: \n49: - [ ] Unit tests for middleware\n50: - [ ] Unit tests for handlers\n51: - [ ] Integration tests for server startup\n52: - [ ] Verify graceful shutdown behavior\n53: \n54: ## Checklist\n55: \n56: - [ ] Code follows Go best practices\n57: - [ ] All exported functions have documentation\n58: - [ ] Error handling is consistent\n59: - [ ] Configuration is externalized\n60: - [ ] Tests cover happy path and error cases\n61: - [ ] No business logic in framework layer\n\n(End of file - total 61 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-004 Implementation Plan\n\n## Phase 1: Project Structure Setup\n\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/` directory structure\n- [ ] Create subpackages: `server/`, `handlers/`, `middleware/`, `config/`\n- [ ] Define interface contracts between layers\n\n## Phase 2: HTTP Server Foundation\n\n- [ ] Implement base server structure with configurable options\n- [ ] Setup HTTP router (choose framework: Gin/Chi/std lib)\n- [ ] Implement server lifecycle (start, stop, graceful shutdown)\n- [ ] Add health check endpoint\n\n## Phase 3: Middleware Implementation\n\n- [ ] Request logging middleware\n- [ ] Error recovery/panic handling middleware\n- [ ] Request ID generation middleware","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-004/plan.md","time":{"start":1775844421230,"end":1775844421252}}}}
